.TH "svc_rdma_rw_ctx_init" 9 "svc_rdma_rw_ctx_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_rdma_rw_ctx_init \- Prepare a R/W context for I/O
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_rdma_rw_ctx_init
.BI "(struct svcxprt_rdma *rdma "  ","
.BI "struct svc_rdma_rw_ctxt *ctxt "  ","
.BI "u64 offset "  ","
.BI "u32 handle "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdma" 12
controlling transport instance
.IP "ctxt" 12
R/W context to prepare
.IP "offset" 12
RDMA offset
.IP "handle" 12
RDMA tag/handle
.IP "direction" 12
I/O direction
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns on success, the number of WQEs that will be needed
on the workqueue, or a negative errno.
